node.text:
Robert and I discuss the idea of prejudices in business and hiring practices.⁣
⁣
Robert Murphy: "...if it really were true that in the United States women only get paid whatever the number is, 88 cents, for the same work. It’s a mystery. How come all the firms that are run by greedy capitalists aren’t hiring just women because they bring in the same output?"⁣
⁣
For more context on this clip and insight into this topic, click the link in my bio to watch the full episode.

node.title: The Market’s Penalty for Irrational Prejudice

On this podcast episode (S4: E43), I am joined by Economist Dr. Robert Murphy.

We cover topics such as value, free trade, private property, and minimum wage laws. We also discuss the specialization of individual tasks, interest rates, the Business Cycle, and more engrossing matters.⁣
⁣
Dr. Robert Murphy is a Mises Institute Senior Fellow, the host of “The Bob Murphy Show”, and an author.⁣
⁣
Click the link in my bio to watch this episode in full.

"I’m not a catastrophist. There are many wonderful people teaching in many institutions around the world... While I say that, the universities have by and large fundamentally forgotten, if not betrayed, their fundamental value proposition."⁣
⁣
My latest podcast with Dr. Stephen Blackwood is now live on YouTube, Apple Podcasts and Spotify. ⁣
⁣
We discuss the inner workings of philosophical aspects about social constructs, the spiritual ‘culture crisis’, what it means to live as an individual in a time of spiritual, cultural crisis, and his experience developing @RalstonCollege.⁣
⁣
Watch or listen via the link in my bio.⁣
⁣
Recorded 05/18/21.
